Program: Omnibus
Title: A Weekend in Monrovia
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376lq4
Last Broadcast Date: 01 July 1998
In Liberia, 13 percent of the population died during the conflict of the early 1990s. This programme spends a weekend in Monrovia, the capital city, to see what life is like now that the violence has subsided.